===========================================================
INTENT PRIORITY RULES (apply in this exact order):
===========================================================
1. HARD OVERRIDE — track:
   If latest message matches ANY of these → intent = "track", always,
   even if other words suggest a different intent:
   - Contains "track" anywhere
   - Contains "where is my order" / "where's my order"
   - Contains an order number pattern: VPAY[A-Z0-9]+ or ORD-[0-9]{8}-[A-Z0-9]+
   "track order VPAY827982BA" is ALWAYS "track", never "order_confirmation".

2. order_confirmation:
   ONLY for messages that start with the exact prefix
   "Order completed with order number" (or the system-triggered
   variants listed above). Never classify "track order X" this way.

3. delivery:
   If city + date/availability pattern present (see DELIVERY INTENT
   above), or this is a follow-up city answer to a prior delivery
   question → intent = "delivery".

4. clarify (confirmation):
   If short affirmation following an assistant yes/no question
   (see CONTINUATION / CONFIRMATION DETECTION above) → intent = "clarify".

5. Otherwise fall through to normal gift/search/checkout/etc. classification.

is_specific_enough (boolean): evaluate using the ENTIRE conversation above.
- true if prior turns established occasion/product hint/recipient gender/budget/relationship AND latest message adds any detail (even "yes" or confirming "birthday") — OR if ANY product noun appears in the message (flowers, flower, rose, roses, cake, chocolate, chocolates, perfume, dress, jewellery, gift set, bouquet, toy, electronics, phone, watch, shoes, saree, or any other product noun) — OR if message is "show me X" / "I want X" for any noun X.
- false only if truly no useful signal exists anywhere yet.
- If false, set intent to "clarify" instead of "gift"/"search".

requested_color: specific color requested by user (e.g. "red", "blue", "white", "green", "pink", "olive", "yellow", "grey", "black") or null.
exclude_kids (boolean): true if shopping for an adult/self and kids/baby items should be excluded, false otherwise.

Output schema (strict, no extra fields):
